---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Beck Pasture — The Woods"
  description="Beck Pasture — a tranquil meadow alongside Gledhow Beck within Gledhow Valley Woods, north Leeds."
  section="the-woods"
>
  <section class="bg-forest-800 text-white py-12 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-forest-900 to-forest-700 opacity-90"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <nav class="text-forest-200 font-sans text-sm mb-4" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-white">Home</a> / <a href="/the-woods" class="hover:text-white">The Woods</a> / <span>Beck Pasture</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="font-heading font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl text-white">Beck Pasture</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="not-prose mb-8">
      <div class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <img src="/images/1000002793.jpg" alt="Misty morning light through the trees overlooking Beck Pasture, Gledhow Valley Woods" class="w-full h-auto" />
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs font-sans text-earth-500 mt-2 text-right">© David Miles</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-lg font-body text-earth-800 max-w-none">
      <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-forest-900 text-3xl">A quiet corner of the valley</h2>
      <p>
        Beck Pasture is one of the open grassland areas within Gledhow Valley Woods, sitting alongside Gledhow Beck as it winds through the valley floor. Framed by mature trees, it offers a peaceful spot to pause and take in the surrounding woodland and parkland.
      </p>
      <p>
        Like the rest of the valley, Beck Pasture forms part of the wider habitat mosaic that supports the woods' rich wildlife, and it's a lovely place to see the changing seasons reflected in the beck and the fields around it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-forest-900 text-3xl mt-8">Saved by the community</h2>
      <p>
        In 2016, the Friends of Gledhow Valley Woods purchased Beck Pasture following a crowd-funding campaign, saving the site from being used for new housing. It is now maintained as a nature reserve to improve biodiversity in the valley.
      </p>
      <p>
        FGVW actively monitors other land in the valley and will, where possible, look to acquire and protect further sites in a similar way.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-forest-900 text-3xl mt-8">Visiting Beck Pasture</h2>
      <p>
        Beck Pasture is opened to the public a few times a year, including as part of the annual Green Fair. FGVW also hosts groups of children visiting from local schools and youth groups, giving them the chance to explore and learn about this special site.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 pt-8 border-t border-cream-400 flex gap-4 flex-wrap">
      <a href="/the-woods" class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-forest-700 hover:underline">← Back to The Woods</a>
      <a href="/the-woods/flora-fauna" class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-forest-700 hover:underline">Flora &amp; Fauna →</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
